t-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Emphasized Text</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Anything that appears within<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;em&gt;...&lt;/em&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>element is displayed as emphasized text.</p><p>\n\n<!--StartFragment--></p><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Marked Text</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Anything that appears with-in<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;mark&gt;...&lt;/mark&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>element, is displayed as marked with yellow ink.</p><p>\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Strong Text</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Anything that appears within<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;strong&gt;...&lt;/strong&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>element is displayed as important text.</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Text Abbreviation</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">You can abbreviate a text by putting it inside opening &lt;abbr&gt; and closing &lt;/abbr&gt; tags. If present, the title attribute must contain this full description and nothing else.</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Acronym Element</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;acronym&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>element allows you to indicate that the text between &lt;acronym&gt; and &lt;/acronym&gt; tags is an acronym.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At present, the major browsers do not change the appearance of the content of the &lt;acronym&gt; element.</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n</p><p>\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Text Direction</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;bdo&gt;...&lt;/bdo&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>element stands for Bi-Directional Override and it is used to override the current text direction.</p><p></p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Special Terms</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;dfn&gt;...&lt;/dfn&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>element (or HTML Definition Element) allows you to specify that you are introducing a special term. It''s usage is similar to italic words in the midst of a paragraph.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Typically, you would use the &lt;dfn&gt; element the first time you introduce a key term. Most recent browsers render the content of a &lt;dfn&gt; element in an italic font.</p><p></p><p>\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Quoting Text</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">When you want to quote a passage from another source, you should put it in between<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;blockquote&gt;...&lt;/blockquote&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>tags.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Text inside a &lt;blockquote&gt; element is usually indented from the left and right edges of the surrounding text, and sometimes uses an italicized font.</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n</p><p>\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Short Quotations</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;q&gt;...&lt;/q&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>element is used when you want to add a double quote within a sentence.</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Text Citations</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If you are quoting a text, you can indicate the source placing it between an opening<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;cite&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>tag and closing<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;/cite&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>tag</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">As you would expect in a print publication, the content of the &lt;cite&gt; element is rendered in italicized text by default.</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n</p><p></p><p>\n\n<!--StartFragment--><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(18, 18, 20); font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: -1px; margin: 0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0px; font-size: 1.7em; line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; text-shadow: rgb(204, 204, 204) 1px 1px 2px; position: relative; left: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Computer Code</h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 24px; margin: 0em 0.2em 0.6em; overflow-wrap: break-word; padding: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 15px !important; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Any programming code to appear on a Web page should be placed inside<span>&nbsp;</span><b style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 640;">&lt;code&gt;...&lt;/code&gt;</b><span>&nbsp;</span>tags. Usually the content of the &lt;code&gt; element is presented in a monospaced font, just like the code in most programming books.</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n</p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n<p></p><p></p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n<p></p><p></p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n<p></p><p></p><p></p><!--EndFragment-->\n\n<p></p>', 4);

